search\",\n 36 |     \"title\": \"Restore or build Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search\",\n 37 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 38 |     \"target\": \"Enterprise Quick Search after hero\",\n 39 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 40 |     \"prompt\": \"Add or restore Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search immediately after the approved hero. This section is mandatory. Preserve the approved hero and all existing landing styles. Build a local, frontend-only AI concierge style search that searches static local content across Industries, Capabilities, Platforms, Build With GFF tools, Resources, and Company pages. Include clickable example searches: Build AI for Banking, Create University AI Lab, Insurance AI, Mining AI, Retail AI, Build AI GCC. Results must appear instantly when typing or clicking examples. Each result must show title, category, short description, and route link. No API calls. No backend. No fake data. Design must be premium, clean, Apple-like, and consistent with the current landing theme. Use subtle Framer Motion or CSS transitions if available. Avoid box-inside-box clutter, excessive pills, badge soup, and neon overload. Mobile must be excellent. Acceptance: section appears after hero, search works locally, examples work, empty state is polished, links resolve, build passes.\"\n 41 |   },\n 42 |   {\n 43 |     \"id\": \"05-homepage-garage-foundry-factory-journey\",\n 44 |     \"title\": \"Complete Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n 45 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 46 |     \"target\": \"Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n 47 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 48 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage transformation journey. It must include Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale. Use the existing approved landing section if one already maps to this. Do not create duplicates. Do not redesign approved sections unnecessarily. Each step should have a concise description, outcome, and route link: Garage /plat